Definition: an antihypertensive drug that blocks the formation of angiotensin II in the kidney, leading to relaxation of the arteries
Example: promotes the excretion of salt and water by inhibiting the activity of the angiotensin converting enzyme; also used to treat congestive heart failure
Synonyms: angiotensin-converting_enzyme_inhibitor, antihypertensive, an, drug, that, blocks, the, formation, of, angiotensin, II, in, kidney, leading, to, relaxation, arteries, promotes, excretion, salt, and, water, by, inhibiting, activity, converting, enzyme, also, used, treat, congestive, heart, failure
Category: noun.artifact
